  "instructions": [
    "preheat the oven to 400f.",
    "in a medium bowl, whisk together cornmeal, gluten-free flour, paprika, garlic powder, onion powder, salt, and black pepper.",
    "in a separate bowl, whisk together buttermilk and eggs.",
    "pour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and stir until just combined.",
    "add the chorizo and stir until coated.",
    "using your hands, shape the mixture into small patties, about 1 1/2 inches in diameter.",
    "place the patties on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.",
    "drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle with parsley.",
    "bake for 15-20 minutes, or until crispy and golden brown.",
    "while the chorizo is baking, prepare the namul by mixing together namul, lemon juice, and cayenne pepper in a small bowl.",
    "serve the crispy chorizo on a lazy susan spinner with the creamy namul on the side.",
    "serve immediately."
  ],
